provenance.p:
The manuscript was sold at auction in  as part of the library of book collector Friedrich Gottlieb Julius von Bülow. Presumably, it had come into von Bülow's possession earlier in the 19th century, when the charterhouse was secularized. In von Bülow's collection the manuscript was listed as no. 447 and in the Carthusian collection as H. 29 (see 
                                    Lehmann (1935)

                                ).
